1. What is Flatpak?

Flatpak is a next-generation utility for software deployment. It runs applications in
an isolated Sandbox environment.

Portability: Works across different Linux distributions.
Security: Protects system via sandboxed isolation.
Up-to-date: Access latest apps without dependency issues


2. Key Commands

[Action Command]

Add Remote: flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub [URL]
Search: flatpak search [app-name]
Install: flatpak install [remote] [app-id]
Run: flatpak run [app-id]
List: flatpak list
Update: flatpak update
Uninstall: flatpak uninstall [app-id]
